AGI - More than 300 pallets of humanitarian aid were first downloaded on the temporary pier mounted by the United States on the coast of Gaza. For his part, Hamas insisted "that no route for the delivery of aid, including the floating pier, is an alternative to routes under Palestinian supervision." After days of blocking humanitarian aid in the Palestinian territory besieged and threatened by famine, the U.S. Army announced the arrival of "about 500 tonnes of aid in the coming days". London has announced that a cargo of British aid has been "transported successfully towards the coast of Gaza at the same time to those of the United States and the United Arab Emirates" through the Cypriot maritime corridor, while France has declared that a ship of the military navy with on board 60 tons of aid, will be discharged on the American pier.
&nbsp;
The Israeli offensive on <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-16/Israeli-announcing-nuove-truppe-rafah-26416471/">Rafah</a> continues: according to Hamas, the Israeli army has made new attacks that have caused the death of two people in the Berber refugee camp. And while the Idf reported the bodies of three Islamic hostages - Shani Louk, Amit Buskila and Itzhak Gelerenter> - "brutally murdered" during the escape from the music festival Nova on October 7, the army announced it was engaged in "floating" in Jabalia, in the northern part of the Gaza Strip.
&nbsp;
<div </div
