In the document are also asked "more efforts" to improve the entry flows of international aid "through all the interested vessels, including Rafah's." The United States, which also oppose the offensive on Rafah, announced for tomorrow the visit to Israel of the National Security Council of the White House, Jake Sullivan, which today will stop in Saudi Arabia. Since Israel has ordered civilians to leave the eastern areas of Rafah on May 6 in anticipation of a major land offensive, "640.000 people" have fled the city, "of which 40,000 on May 16", according to the Israeli office for humanitarian affairs of the United Nations (Ocha).&nbsp;&nbsp;
